Daniels Igoni, Yenagoa Bayelsa State Governor, Seriake Dickson, has said he will leverage on agriculture and Small and Medium Scale Enterprises to realise the prosperity agenda of his administration. He said this during the maiden meeting of his newly constituted cabinet at the Government House, Yenagoa, on Wednesday. This was sequel to the swearing in of his 24 commissioners on Tuesday. The Commissioner for Information and Orientation, Mr. Ayibaina Duba, who addressed journalists after the meeting, said, “The governor challenged the new cabinet members to realise that they have enormous responsibilities that require their creativity and ingenuity to deliver the prosperity agenda of the administration through their different ministries.” Copyright PUNCH.
